Sprint reviews Step 1: Define &lsquo;done&rsquo; As a regular user of Jira, there&rsquo;s nothing more satisfying to me than moving a task from &lsquo;code review&rsquo; to &lsquo;done.&rsquo; That swoosh of an agile card represents completed work we set out to accomplish as a team. Done and done!
{#7065159f .component__image}
Crossing the finish line and completing work requires good planning, a clear definition of &lsquo;done,&rsquo; and focused execution. Most of this happens during sprint planning, but to have a successful sprint review and sprint, teams need to do a little more than plan.
